attributes.value: Steve Lyman brings you 5 more iconic jazz licks that will blow your mind!
In this lesson, Raghav will teach you various hand techniques and how to properly develop them to be able to play a lot of different advanced patterns on the kit.
In this lesson, Alex shares four tips with you that will help learn harder songs a lot faster.
In this lesson, Reuben Spyker will teach you how to get thirty different sounds from your snare drum, without relying on tuning.
In this lesson, Raghav is going to share six tips with you that will help you be as prepared as possible for your first live gig.
Practice Until You Cannot Get It Wrong
In this lesson, Daru Jones goes over why he sets up his kit as he does and how looking to look different might give you an upper hand when it comes to marketability.
In this lesson, Stephane will teach you why learning rolls is such an important part of being a drummer.
In this lesson, Raghav will share a few tips with you, that will help you become a way better musician in the long run.

In this lesson, Gregg will teach you about the importance of vocalizing drum patterns, when it comes to learning how to play different licks and grooves, playing what you hear in your head and what you read on a chart.
In this lesson, Jared will teach you eight tips to take in consideration when practicing on electronic kits,
In this lesson, Gleb Sobel will teach you how to play double strokes dynamically with your hands and feet, to enrich the sound of your grooves and make them feel a lot better.

In this lesson, Jared will teach you five drum beats that drummers tend to struggle with a lot, regardless of skill level. Along the way, he will discuss what exactly makes these grooves so hard to play and what you can do to overcome those hurdles.
Beat #1 - Paul Simon - "50 Ways To Leave Your Lover"
In this lesson, Larnell will take you through the process he follows when he's learning songs and coming up with parts that best complement them.
In this lesson, Dorothea will teach you how to execute the back-stick stick trick. This is a very popular stick trick among drum corps aficionados that looks really cool and impressive.
In this lesson, Dave is going to teach you eight warm-ups: three with and five without a kit. These are great to get you warmed up for gigs or practice sessions.

In this lesson, Jared is going to give you his first impressions on 14 drum products. This includes the Big Fat Neck Tie, the Spinball, the Snareweight, Cympads, the Tama QR Cymbal Nut, the SwitchKick, DrumTacs, the DrumDial, the Neary Drum Torque, K-brakes, the Slap Stick, the Cymb-o-mute, the Low Boy Beater, and the Junk Hat.
In this lesson, Glen Sobel is going to teach you some of his favorite stick tricks.
In this lesson, Larnell Lewis will teach you the intricacies behind his foot technique for playing double strokes with one foot.
In this lesson, Dorothea will teach you how to play cheeselets, a very popular hybrid rudiment among the drum corp community.

Ten styles. Ten kits. One take. Drummers start your engines! Theres your regular old Grand Prix, and then theres the Grand Prix of drumming. Watch Brandon Toews, author of The Drummers Toolbox (which teaches you to play 100+ styles on drums) play 10 musical styles in just 10 minutes: Rock, Blues, Jazz, Afro-Brazilian, Metal, Country, Afro-Cuban, Afro-Caribbean, Funk, and Electronic. If that isnt crazy enough for you, watch Brandons pit crew change his set-up in between each style. Have you ever changed a drum kit in 30 seconds?
